d perhaps succeed within the confines of the Japanese corporation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aJapanese fiction. 0aJapanese literaturey20th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aambition.  aasian.  abusiness.  abusinessmen.  acareer.  acorporate culture.  acorporate japan.  acorporate world.  acorporation.  aeconomics.  aentrepreneurial spirit.  aethics.  afiction.  ajapan.  ajapanese.  aliterary criticism.  amanagerial ranks.  amedia.  amoney and power.  anovel.  apower and wealth.  apower.  aprofessionals.  ashoshamen.  asogo shosha.  asuccess.  atrading.  atranslated.1 aMulhern, Chieko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Archive (pre 2000) eBook Packagez978311064968008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052091051540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520910515423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520910515/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  a978-3-11-064968-0  Asian Studies Archive (pre 2000) eBook Package  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles